<p>I have a div with an inline background style. I want to prevent this background image from loading as long as JS is enabled, to use less data, but let it load if JS is disabled. I also want to be able to get the URL of the image later on using jQuery.</p>  <p>I currently have this in a <code>&lt;script&gt;</code> element in my <code>&lt;head&gt;</code>, so that it works as quickly as possible (adapted from <a href="http://stackoverflow.com/a/23594971/3217306">this answer on SO</a>):</p>  <p><strong>JS</strong></p>  <pre><code>function removeBackgroundImagesBeforeTheyLoad() {       var divs = document.getElementsByTagName("div");       for (var i = 0; i &lt; divs.length; i++) {           divs[i].style.removeProperty("background");       } } // Fire the function every microsecond var timer = setInterval(function() {      removeBackgroundImagesBeforeTheyLoad(); }, 1); // Stop firing the function after 3 secs setTimeout(function() {     clearInterval(timer); }, 3000); </code></pre>  <p>This hides the image, but still allows it to load.</p>